--- On Wed, 17 Oct 2007, Sioud, Mongi wrote:
> We are implementing a digital collection system to BAnQ library Quebec
> Canada (Biblioth=E8que et Archives Nationales du Qu=E9bec) www.banq.qc.ca
> <http://www.banq.qc.ca/>  and we want to use ARK Persistent Identifier
> Scheme. To do this we need a NAAN. Can you, please, assign a number in
> the name of National Library and Archives of Quebec? For more
> information please contact Mongi Sioud at mongi.sioud@cgi.com.


Hi Mongi,

Thanks for your message.  The NAAN,

=0952327

has been registered for the Biblioth=E8que et Archives Nationales du Qu=E9b=
ec
and you may begin using it immediately.

In thinking about how to manage the namespace, you may find it helpful
to consider the usual practice of partitioning it with reserved prefixes
of, say 1-5 characters, eg, names of the form "ark:/52327/xt...." for
one "sub-publisher" in an organization.  Opaque prefixes that only have
meaning to information professionals are often a good idea and have
precedent in schemes such as ISBN and ISSN.

There's nothing else you need to do right now.  As you may know, we're
hoping to craft a small number of standardized statements for name
assigning authority policy that organizations can use if they want to.

-John


